               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-619" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-619" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-619" type="surname" value="SABBARTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-619" type="given" value="JOSHUA"></interp>JOSHUA SABBARTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cabinet-maker, and live in Bagnigge-wells-road. On the afternoon of the 15th of November I met the prisoner in the road, with a plane, which I knew to be mine—I ran after him—he station-house the plane was picked up and given to me—this is it—it was lost from my father's front shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. JONES</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Is it yours or your father's? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi>
               </p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183611280098"></xptr>
               <p>Mine—I have had it seven years—there were two other boys walking with him, who ran away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you worked with the plane? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—for the last seven years—I had seen it about half an hour before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-620" type="witnessName">
